The course aims at an extensive development of vocabulary for use in different situations (in the court, at a notary's office or a company) and provides further practice in reading legal texts. The main emphasis is on developing legal terminology both in the oral and written form. Conversation topics: crimes in different countries, classification of crimes, criminals. Grammar categories: numerals, weeks and months, time, dates, age, nationality, personal, possessive and interrogative pronouns, everyday words and expressions (different questions, explanation, warning, agreement, disagreement).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general aim: to acquire legal terminology for the course themes, to develop reading, translating and communication skills and to upgrade grammar skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students can:
* understand short and simple legal documents and other texts related to their future professions;
* find relevant information from texts;
* exchange relevant information and express their opinions regarding legal problems;
* express their points of view;
* correctly use the terminology and grammar acquired during the course;
* translate simpler documents and other professional texts,
* take part in discussion regarding the course themes;
* use the acquired terminology both in oral and written form.
